Diun allows monitoring a Docker image for new updates. To opt in to watching a task's Docker image, include the diun.enable label: config { labels = { "diun.enable" = "true" }
} By default, this will only watch the current tag of the image. If the tag is latest, Diun will send a notification when that tag's checksum changes. To allow Diun to watch other tags, include additional labels: config { labels = { "diun.enable" = "true" "diun.watch_repo" = "true" "diun.max_tags" = 3 }
} This will let Diun watch all tags in the Docker repo. It is highly recommended to set a maximum number of tags that Diun should watch, otherwise Diun will watch ALL tags, including older ones. See Diun for more information on configuring Diun.

