This section is relevant if the application requires KV secrets from Vault. It uses the Vault Terraform module . Firstly, add the relevant KV secrets to Vault. Next, create and add a Vault policy for read-only access to the relevant KV secrets: # terraform/vault/policies/nomad_app.hcl
path "kvv2/data/prod/nomad/app" { capabilities = ["read"]
} # terraform/vault/policies.tf
resource "vault_policy" "nomad_app" { name = "nomad_app" policy = file("policies/nomad_app.hcl")
} Include the vault and template blocks in the Nomad jobspec: vault { policies = ["nomad_app"]
} template { data = <<EOF
{{ with secret "kvv2/data/prod/nomad/app" }}
AUTH="{{ .Data.data.username }}":"{{ .Data.data.password }}"
{{ end }}
EOF destination = "secrets/auth.env" env = true
} This will access the Vault secrets and include them as the AUTH environment variable in the job.

